===============================================
NEUROSENSE PDF TEMPLATE PLACEMENT INSTRUCTIONS
===============================================

TO ENABLE TEMPLATE-BASED PDF GENERATION:

1. Create or obtain your PDF template file
   - Must be named: Neurosense Report.pdf
   - Must be multi-page PDF (minimum 2 pages recommended)
   - Should have professional letterhead, logo, branding

2. Place the file in this directory:
   server/assets/pdf-templates/Neurosense Report.pdf

3. Restart the server
   - The system will automatically detect the template
   - Console will show: "✨ Using template-based PDF generator"

4. Customize coordinates (optional):
   - Edit: server/config/pdfCoordinates.js
   - Adjust X, Y positions for each data field
   - See README.md for detailed guide

===============================================
TEMPLATE DESIGN SPECIFICATIONS
===============================================

Page Size: A4 (595.28 x 841.89 points)
Format: PDF
Recommended Pages: 2-3 pages

Page 1 - Cover Page:
  - Patient name, ID, date, age, gender
  - Clinic name and logo
  - Professional letterhead

Page 2 - Numbers at a Glance:
  - Overall score display area
  - 7 brain parameters with scores
  - Classification indicators

Page 3 - Brain Type (Optional):
  - Brain type name and description
  - Recommendations section

===============================================
QUICK TEST
===============================================

After placing template:
1. Upload QEEG files through the web interface
2. Click "Execute Calculation"
3. Click "Save and Download PDF"
4. Check generated PDF to verify layout

